# Agency Standards — [Agency Name]

> This file defines agency-wide coding standards and practices.
> All client projects inherit from these standards unless explicitly overridden in the project's own CLAUDE.md.

## Universal Standards

### Code Quality
<!-- Standards that apply regardless of stack -->
- All code must pass linting before commit
- No commented-out code in production branches
- No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or credentials — use environment variables
- All public functions should have clear parameter names (self-documenting)

### Git Workflow
<!-- How the agency works with git across all projects -->
- Branch naming: `[type]/[description]` (e.g., `feature/user-auth`, `fix/payment-timeout`)
- Commit messages: [describe your convention]
- PR required for all changes to main/production branches
- Minimum 1 reviewer per PR

### Code Review Standards
<!-- What reviewers should check for -->
- Correctness: does the code do what the PR says it does?
- Security: no injection vulnerabilities, proper auth checks, no exposed secrets
- Performance: no obvious N+1 queries, no unnecessary re-renders, proper caching
- Consistency: follows project conventions (check project's CLAUDE.md)
- Client constraints: respects any compliance or deployment restrictions

### Testing Baseline
<!-- Minimum testing expectations across all projects -->
- Critical paths must have tests (auth, payments, data mutations)
- Tests must pass in CI before merge
- Test naming: `[what]_[scenario]_[expected]` or framework-appropriate equivalent

### Security Baseline
<!-- Security practices all projects must follow -->
- OWASP Top 10 awareness
- Input validation at system boundaries
- Authentication and authorization on all protected endpoints
- No sensitive data in logs
- Dependencies audited for known vulnerabilities

